d%20created%20%26quot%3Ba%20toxic%20culture%20of%20lying%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-member-details-sam-altman-lied-allegation-ousted-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eengaging%20in%20psychologically%20abusive%20behavior%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%20the%20two%20current%20board%20members%20said%20they%20had%20found%20Altman%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20forthcoming%20on%20all%20relevant%20issues%20and%20consistently%20collegial%20with%20his%20management%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20published%20the%20same%20day%20as%20her%20op-ed%2C%20Toner%20explained%20why%20the%20former%20board%20previously%20decided%20to%20remove%20Altman%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20lied%20to%20them%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%20times%26quot%3B%20and%20withheld%20information.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20the%20old%20OpenAI%20board%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-learned-of-chatgpt-release-on-twitter-helen-toner-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20out%20about%20ChatGPT's%20release%20on%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20perhaps%20difficult%20to%20remember%20now%2C%20Openai%20released%20Chatgpt%20in%20November%202022%20as%20a%20research%20project%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20how%20useful%20its%20models%20are%20in%20conversational%20settings%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20and%20Summers%20wrote%20in%20response.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20built%20on%20gpt-3.5%2C%20an%20existing%20ai%20model%20which%20had%20already%20been%20available%20for%20more%20than%20eight%20months%20at%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToner%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20ahead%20of%20publication.%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20supports%20%26quot%3Beffective%20regulation%20of%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%26quot%3B%20and%20Altman%2C%20who%20was%20reinstated