sinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-we-evaluate-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221442%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22katie%20oelker%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659850eb6979d7371820e889%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22721%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20Katie%20Oelker%2C%20left%2C%20with%20her%20husband.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Katie%20Oelker%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20little%20over%20a%20year%20after%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20bought%20our%20house%2C%20we%20refinanced%20our%20mortgage.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERefinancing%20means%20paying%20closing%20costs%20again%2C%20but%20we'll%20break%20even%20after%20just%20four%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20could%20pay%20off%20our%2030-year%20mortgage%20in%20just%2023%20years%20with%20the%20money%20we%20save%2C%20but%20we're%20putting%20it%20in%20a%20brokerage%20account.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20bought%20our%20second%20home%20at%20the%20end%20of%202019%2C%20we%20were%20excited%20about%20the%20lower%20interest%20rate%20compared%20to%20our%20first%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20we%20were%20postponing%20our%20debt-payoff%20goals%20and%20taking%20on%20a%20higher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20moving%20to%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate%20would%20offset%20some%20of%20the%20interest%20we%20would%20be%20paying%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20We%20were%20comfortable%20with%20the%20new%20payment%2C%20but%20the%20lower%20rate%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20stomach%20the%20higher%20monthly%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20moved%20and%20were%20enjoying%20our%20new%20home%2C%20we%20didn't%20really%20think%20twice%20about%20our%20interest%20rate%3B%20we'd%20gone%20from%204.125%25%20to%203.875%25%2C%20so%20we%20felt%20pretty%20good.%20It%20had%20been%20less%20than%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20since%20we%20bought%20our%20home%2C%20so%20refinancing%20was%20never%20on%20our%20radar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20spring%20of%202021%2C%20however%2C%20we%20realized%20we%20could%20likely%20get%20an%20even%20lower%20rate%20and%20decided%20to%20go%20through%20the%20refinance%20process.%20Rates%20had%20continued%20to%20drop%2C%20and%20we%20realized%20we%20wanted%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20low%20rates%20before%20they%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcurrent-mortgage-refinance-rates%5C%22%3ERefinancing%20our%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20allowed%20us%20to%20go%20from%20a%203.875%25%20to%20a%202.875%25%2030-year%20fixed%20mortgage%2C%20shaving%201%25%20off%20our%20mortgage%20interest%20rate.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20lowered%20our%20payments%20from%20%242%2C366%20to%20%242%2C141%20a%20month.%20While%20that%20may%20not%20seem%20like%20a%20lot%2C%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20every%20month%20can%20add%20up%2C%20especially%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20refinancing%20our%20mortgage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERefinancing%20has%20pros%20and%20cons%2C%20and%20the%20decision%20to%20do%20so%20was%20one%20we%20didn't%20take%20lightly.%20One%20of%20the%20cons%20is%20that%20you%20typically%20have%20to%20repay%20closing%20costs.%20Anyone%20who%20has%20closed%20on%20a%20home%20knows%20that%20closing%20costs%20are%20typically%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20justify%20paying%20closing%20costs%20again%2C%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgage-broker%5C%22%3Emortgage%20broker%3C%2Fa%3E%20informed%20us%20that%20we%20would%20break%20even%20in%20four%20years.%20This%20meant%20the%20amount%20we%20paid%20in%20closing%20costs%20wrapped%20into%20our%20mortgage%20payment%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bpaid%20off%26quot%3B%20in%20four%20years.%20Because%20we%20plan%20on%20living%20in%20our%20home%20for%20much%20longer%20than%20four%20years%2C%20we%20knew%20that%20we%20would%20benefit%20from%20a%20lower%20rate%20and%20increased%20monthly%20savings%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20one%20of%20the%20pros%20of%20refinancing%20is%20applying%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate%20to%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20mortgage.%20Since%20we%20are%20only%2016%20months%20into%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E30-year%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20will%20have%20a%20long%20time%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20lower%20rate.%20This%20lower%20rate%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20means%20a%20lower%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3ECheck%20today's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%3E%20average%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20amount%20of%20house%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20we're%20doing%20with%20the%20money%20we%20save%20each%20month%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20people%20refinance%20and%20then%20spend%20the%20money%20they%20save%20each%20month%20elsewhere%2C%20we've%20decided%20to%20put%20it%20into%20a%20separate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20way%2C%20we%20can%20use%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%20in%20a%20lump%20sum%20once%20it%20reaches%20the%20balance%2C%20or%20we%20can%20use%20the%20investment%20money%20to%20fuel%20our%20early%20retirement%20goals%20if%20we%20decide%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20refinancing%2C%20we%20will%20shave%20off%20around%20%2420%2C000%20in%20interest%20over%2030%20years.%20If%20we%20put%20the%20extra%20%24225%20a%20month%20toward%20our%20mortgage%2C%20we%20could%20save%20around%20%2426%2C000%20in%20interest%20and%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%20seven%20years%20early%2C%20in%20about%2023%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20is%20incredible%20savings%2C%20we%20figure%20if%20we%20can%20invest%20the%20extra%20money%20at%20an%20estimated%207%25%20stock%20market%20return%2C%20that%20money%20should%20grow%20to%20about%20%24145%2C000%20in%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20time%20(23%20years).%20While%20we%20still%20plan%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%2C%20investing%20the%20extra%20money%20versus%20applying%20it%20directly%20to%20the%20mortgage%20will%20help%20us%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20the%20money%20we%20save.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetirement%20Planning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-robo-advisors%5C%22%3E%20best%20robo%20advisors%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20start%20your%20retirement%20planning%20journey.%20Institutions%20like%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Frobinhood-investing-review%5C%22%3E%20Robinhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsofi-invest-review%5C%22%3ESoFi%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20offer%20an%20IRA%20match%20to%20help%20your%20savings%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20March%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-decided-not-pay-off-mortgage-early-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717106882000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6063329fc9d73b00186e9205%3Ffo