s%20he%20faces%2034%20counts%20of%20forging%20business%20documents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmother-teresa-could-not-trump-compares-himself-to-saint-in-hush-money-case%2Farticleshow%2F110566736.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmother-teresa-could-not-trump-compares-himself-to-saint-in-hush-money-case%2Famp_articleshow%2F110566736.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmother-teresa-could-not-trump-compares-himself-to-saint-in-hush-money-case%2Famp_articleshow%2F110566736.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BFelt%20Like%20It%20Was%20Raining%20Fire%26quot%3B%3A%20Residents%20Of%20India's%20'Hottest'%20Place%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20nondescript%20area%20of%20Mungeshpur%20in%20northwest%20Delhi%20was%20thrust%20into%20the%20limelight%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20when%20the%20temperature%20recorded%20by%20an%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20weather%20station%20in%20the%20area%20was%20a%20staggering%2052.9%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20making%20it%20a%20record%20not%20just%20for%20the%20national%20capital%2C%20but%20also%20for%20all%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20IMD%20has%20said%20it%20is%20checking%20the%20temperature%20sensor%20in%20the%20observatory%2C%20especially%20since%20it%20was%20an%20outlier%20compared%20to%20the%20other%20weather%20stations%20in%20Delhi%2C%20people%20in%20Mungeshpur%20said%20that%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20final%20figure%2C%20Wednesday%20was%20indeed%20the%20hottest%20it%20has%20ever%20been%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20residents%20told%20NDTV%20that%20several%20people%2C%20including%20children%2C%20had%20to%20be%20hospitalised%20because%20of%20heatstroke%20and%20other%20heat-related%20issues.%20What%20made%20things%20worse%2C%20they%20said%2C%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20area%20did%20not%20have%20electricity%20all%20of%20Wednesday%20night%20after%20a%20transformer%20exploded%20at%2011%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJai%20Narayan%2C%20who%20works%20at%20Jawahar%20Navodaya%20School%20in%20Mungeshpur%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20temperature%20was%20indeed%20very%20high%20on%20May%2029%20and%20some%20people%20from%20the%20meteorological%20department%20came%20and%20checked%20the%20sensor%20at%20night.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhawani%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20hardware%20shop%20in%20the%20area%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20heatwave%20has%20been%20very%20intense%20this%20time%20and%20it%20has%20been%20over%2045%20degrees%20consistently.%20Yesterday%20did%20feel%20like%20it%20was%20over%2050%20degrees.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20local%20resident%2C%20Vijay%2C%20who%20is%2065%20years%20old%2C%20said%20many%20of%20his%20family%20members%20fell%20ill%20because%20of%20the%20heat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20transformer%20exploded%20around%2011%20pm.%20All%20of%20us%20and%20all%20the%20children%20in%20the%20area%20had%20to%20suffer%20without%20power%20in%20the%20heat.%20Many%20people%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20to%20hospitals.%20It%20felt%20like%20it%20was%20raining%20fire%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20shopkeepers%2C%20much%20like%20the%20heat%2C%20it's%20been%20a%20case%20of%20extremes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERohit%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20general%20store%2C%20said%20he%20has%20seen%20a%20rise%20in%20his%20business%20because%20cold%20water%20bottles%20and%20soft%20drinks%20are%20selling%20like%20hotcakes.%20%26quot%3BA%20record%20has%20been%20broken.%20We%20have%20never%20experienced%20temperatures%20as%20high%20as%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhupendra%20is%20from%20Bihar%20and%20runs%20a%20cycle%20repair%20shop%20in%20the%20area.%20He%20said%20business%20is%20down%20since%20no%20one%20is%20stepping%20out%20in%20the%20afternoons%20because%20of%20the%20heat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Wait%20For%20Final%20Figure'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIMD%20chief%20M%20Mohapatra%2C%20however%2C%20said%20the%20figure%20of%2052.9%20degrees%20should%20not%20be%20treated%20as%20final%20and%20that%20the%20sensors%20are%20being%20checked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMungeshpur%20was%20an%20outlier.%20We%20have%2017%20observatories%20in%20Delhi%20and%20the%20temperature%20in%20Mungeshpur%20was%20very%20different%20from%20the%20rest.%20Delhi%20has%20never%20seen%20such%20high%20temperatures%2C%20the%20previous%20high%20was%2048.4%20degrees%20in%20Palam.%20This%20is%20why%20checking%20the%20data%20is%20a%20must%2C%20I%20would%20request%20everyone%20to%20wait%20for%20that%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Mohapatra%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717081500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F7khv0al8_mungeshpur_625x300_30_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffelt-like-it-was-raining-fire-residents-of-mungeshpur-indias-hottest-place-5780880%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20nondescript%20area%20of%20Mungeshpur%20in%20northwest%20Delhi%20was%20thrust%20into%20the%20limelight%20on%20Wednesday%20when%20the%20temperature%20recorded%20by%20an%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20weather%20station%20in%20the%20area%20was%20a%20staggering%2052.9%20degrees%20Celsius.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffelt-like-it-was-raining-fire-residents-of-mungeshpur-indias-hottest-place-5780880%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffelt-like-it-was-raining-fire-residents-of-mungeshpur-indias-hottest-place-5780880%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffelt-like-it-was-raining-f