%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%20the%20hard%20work%2C%20Uttarakhand-based%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20was%20delighted%20that%20his%20eatery%20would%20finally%20be%20inaugurated%20soon.%20But%20fate%20had%20other%20plans.%20%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%2C%20my%20eatery%20was%20ravaged%20by%20floods%20in%20the%202013%20natural%20disaster.%20The%20road%20was%20blocked%20for%20six%20months.%20Everything%20was%20reduced%20to%20ruins%20and%20my%20restaurant%20was%20shut%20a%20week%20before%20the%20opening%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandeep%20was%20devastated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20he%20had%20quit%20his%20engineering%20career%20in%20Delhi%20to%20move%20back%20to%20his%20quaint%20hometown%20of%20Nainital%20and%20run%20a%20restaurant.%20Now%2C%20he%20was%20left%20without%20any%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20after%20the%20floods%2C%20as%20he%20was%20passing%20through%20a%20field%2C%20he%20noticed%20a%20few%20women%20labourers%20eating%20%3Cem%3Eroti%20%3C%2Fem%3E(flatbread)%20with%20onions%20and%20%3Cem%3Episyun%20loon%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F187720%2Futtarakhand-flavoured-salt-pisi-loon-traditional-food-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epahadi%20%3C%2Fem%3Esalt%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehand%20grounded%20on%20%3Cem%3Esilbatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20(traditional%20grinding%20stone).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20offered%20me%20the%20%3Cem%3Echapati%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20salt%20made%20with%20garlic%20and%20green%20chillies.%20It%20was%20extremely%20tasty.%20I%20also%20ate%20%3Cem%3Ekakdi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Armenian%20cucumber)%20with%20this%20salt.%20Then%2C%20I%20realised%20it%20is%20this%20salt%20that%20makes%20%3Cem%3Epahadi%20%3C%2Fem%3Efood%20so%20flavoursome.%20I%20recalled%20how%20my%20mother%20would%20pack%20this%20salt%20whenever%20I%20went%20out%20of%20town%20for%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20realised%20no%20one%20ha